Will that site give me more information than I can get by conversing with you like this?
You can go to that website for more information, yes.

The DMV does not collect sales tax when you apply for a vehicle registration if NY State sales tax was paid to a NY State dealer and will, for that reason, not issue a sales tax receipt.

When you register your vehicle you must either pay the sales tax, prove that the sales tax was paid, or prove that your vehicle registration is exempt from sales tax.

You will use the Sales Tax Ememption form at NY State Department of Tax and Finance DTF-803 to receive a non-resident exemption from NY State sales tax.
